==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Oscillograph
<hw>Os"cil*lo*graph</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>oscillare</ets> to swing + <ets>-graph</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>An apparatus for recording or indicating
alternating-current wave forms or other electrical oscillations,
especially of voltages or currents; it usually consists of a
galvanometer with strong field, in which the mass of the moving part is
very small and frequency of vibration very high.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Os`cil*lo*graph"ic</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oscillometer</ent>⟦br⟧
